source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/barramundi-with-pineapple-salsa-5d14dfd7fca63a001616bc32
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
---

2 unit Scallions
½ cup Jasmine Rice
4 ounce Pineapple
6 ounce Green Beans
1 unit Lime
10 ounce Barramundi
1 teaspoon Southwest Spice Blend
4 teaspoon Vegetable Oil
1 tablespoon Butter
Salt
Pepper

Adjust rack to top position and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Trim and thinly slice scallions,
separating whites from greens. Heat a
drizzle of oil in a small pot over mediumhigh
heat. Add scallion whites; cook 30
seconds to 1 minute. Stir in rice and ¾ cup
water (1½ cups for 4 servings). Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook until tender, 15-18 minutes.

Meanwhile, drain pineapple over a
small bowl, reserving juice. Roughly chop
fruit. Trim green beans. Zest and quarter
lime (quarter both limes for 4 servings).
In a separate small bowl, combine
pineapple, scallion greens, lime zest
to taste, juice from 1 lime wedge, and
2 TBSP pineapple juice (3 TBSP for 4).
Season with salt and pepper.

Toss green beans on a baking sheet
with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
Roast on top rack until browned and
tender, 12-15 minutes.

Pat fish dry with paper towels;
season all over with salt and pepper.
Season flesh side with Southwest Spice;
rub to evenly coat.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large
pan over medium-high heat. Add fish,
skin sides down. Cook until skin is crispy,
4-5 minutes. (TIP: Lower heat if skin
begins to brown too quickly.) Flip and
cook until fish is opaque and cooked
through, 2-3 minutes. Turn off heat;
transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in 1 TBSP
butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings), juice from
1 lime wedge and as much remaining
lime zest as you like. Season with
salt and pepper. Divide rice, fish, and
green beans between plates. Top fish
with salsa. Serve with remaining lime
wedges on the side.